title.narrative: Capacity of key government institutions to provide quality health, HIV, Nutrition, education and birth registration services increased.

description.narrative: Essential newborn care coverage including provision of early child development and birth registration services increased from one region in 2018 to four (100%) in 2019 through capacity building of health care workers in 100 per cent (11) public health facilities offering maternity services. Vaccine management was enhanced through capacity building of 67 per cent health facilities providing immunisation services. Community system for follow up of HIV positive mothers and their babies was strengthened nationwide contributing to reduction of mother child transmission of HIV from 7.8 per cent in 2018 to 4.8 per cent in 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/12/2019
